Not later than June 30 of each year, the Society shall report to the Commissioner and to the General Assembly:
salaries and other compensation paid to officers, executives, and directors for the preceding calendar year;
summary and detailed financial statement for the four preceding calendar years indicating amounts for and changes in:
insurance reserves and losses;
assets and liabilities;
income and expenses; and
return on invested surplus; and
management's evaluation of the financial position of the Society which shall include an analysis indicating whether sufficient resources exist to justify providing a dividend or similar distribution to members in the current year and, if not, how the current circumstances vary from prior years in which such distributions have been made.
